CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper September 27, 1958, pg. 28, reads: "Marching Dolls - Pretty girls and marching bands were very much in evidence on Downtown streets Monday afternoon as thousands of Pittsburghers turned out for the parade honoring the Pittsburgh Pirates. Above is a group of charming majorettes from South High School. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Majorettes or cheerleaders from South High School holding megaphones and marching in parade honoring Pittsburgh Pirates, in front of People's First National Bank, Fifth Avenue, Downtown
